{
  "plan": "Eirik completes his turn with a critical hit from his mace attack against Corrupted Ranger Thane. Player rolled a natural 20, so damage is 2d6 (6,5) + 2 = 13 bludgeoning. Thane's HP drops from 26 to 13. Eirik's turn is over. Next in initiative: Corrupted Wolf (5), followed by Scout Kira (3), then Corrupted Stag (1). Both the wolf and stag are uninjured and poised to strike. Corrupted Wolf will use Bite on Eirik (attack roll 9+4=13, miss vs AC 17). Kira will fire a shortbow at Shadow (attack roll 12+6=18, hit vs AC 12). Damage 1d6 [2] + 3 = 5. Shadow HP 16 -> 11. Corrupted Stag acts last, using Gore (attack roll 19+5=24, hit vs Kira AC 15). Damage 2d6 [6,5] + 3 = 14. Kira HP 24 -> 10. After all have acted, increment round to 2.",
  "narration": "Emboldened by the surge of radiant energy, you step in and bring your mace down with brutal precision. The blow smashes through Thane’s guard and cracks against his battered armor, sending a shockwave through his corrupted form. Thane staggers, blood and shadow mingling at his feet—a man caught between two dooms.\n\nThe corrupted wolf lunges for your throat, but its jaws snap shut on empty air, thwarted by your battered shield. Kira, quick as a flash, pivots and lets fly an arrow—the shaft strikes the Shadow, passing through its wraith-flesh with a hiss of radiant pain. The Shadow recoils, tattered and lessened, but still very much a threat. \n\nJust as hope flickers, the corrupted stag thunders into the fray. It lowers its antlers and charges Kira, goring her and tossing her to the muddy ground. She bites back a scream, blood streaking her side, but grits her teeth and shouts, 'I’m still here! Don’t let them surround us!'\n\nAll enemies remain standing, but Thane is badly wounded and the Shadow is hurt. Kira staggers but remains defiant. The camp trembles with violence as round 2 begins—darkness and light warring for every heartbeat.",
  "combat_round": 2,
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateEncounter",
      "parameters": {
        "encounterId": "NC04-E1",
        "changes": "Corrupted Ranger Thane takes another critical hit from Eirik's mace for 13 bludgeoning (HP 26 -> 13). Corrupted Wolf attacks Eirik with Bite (9+4=13) but misses. Scout Kira hits Shadow with shortbow (12+6=18, 1d6[2]+3=5 damage; Shadow HP 16 -> 11). Corrupted Stag gores Kira (19+5=24, 2d6[6,5]+3=14 damage; Kira HP 24 -> 10)."
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "scout_kira",
        "changes": "Takes 14 piercing damage from Corrupted Stag's goring attack (HP 24 -> 10)."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "plan": "Round 2, Shadow (16) acts next, but the player (Eirik) is using a free action to attempt to reach Thane with a commanding, empathetic call in the heat of battle. This does not consume an action and is a roleplaying/narrative moment. The DM will narrate Thane’s reaction, but Thane is still under the corruption’s influence. Next, Shadow will use its Strength Drain attack (attack 18+4=22) against Eirik (AC 17), which is a hit. Damage: 2d6 [4,6]+2=12 necrotic. Eirik must also make a DC 10 Constitution saving throw or have his Strength score reduced by 2d6 (player must roll this save). After Shadow, Thane will act with Multiattack, then Eirik’s turn, then the wolf, Kira, and stag. DO NOT prompt for player action until Eirik’s turn.",
  "narration": "As battle rages, you plant your feet, raising your voice above the howl of corruption and the crash of antlers. 'Ranger! Feel the pain—it means you still live! Remember your oath to your brethren. Resist this darkness and fight for the living!'\n\nFor a fleeting instant, something flickers in Thane’s tortured eyes—a flash of recognition, a tremor in the hand that clutches his blade. His breath rasps and his lips part, as if searching for a word, but the corruption surges and his body seizes, forcing him back into the fray. Whether your words will have any effect, you cannot yet know.\n\nThe Shadow, sensing your distraction, lashes out. Its grasping claws pass through your armor and into your very soul. The cold is absolute—a deathly chill that threatens to sap your strength and will. The creature hits you with a necrotic Strength Drain, dealing a jolt of pain and weakening you with every heartbeat.\n\nEirik, you take 12 necrotic damage. Roll a Constitution saving throw (DC 10). If you fail, the Shadow’s touch will sap your strength further, perhaps permanently. The battlefield churns with violence, and Thane’s fate may still hang in the balance.",
  "combat_round": 2,
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "eirik_hearthwise",
        "changes": "Takes 12 necrotic damage from the Shadow's Strength Drain attack. Must make a DC 10 Constitution saving throw or suffer Strength reduction."
      }
    }
  ]
}
